00:01:19.66,00:01:22.79
"France 1916"

00:01:22.87,00:01:25.75
War began between Germany and France...

00:01:25.83,00:01:28.96
on August 3, 1914.

00:01:29.04,00:01:31.88
Five weeks later, the German army[br]had smashed its way...

00:01:31.92,00:01:34.42
to within 18 miles of Paris.

00:01:34.46,00:01:38.68
There the battered French miraculously[br]rallied at the Marne River...

00:01:38.76,00:01:43.10
and in a series of unexpected[br]counterattacks, drove the Germans back.

00:01:43.18,00:01:45.60
The front was stabilized[br]and shortly afterwards...

00:01:45.68,00:01:49.39
developed into a continuous line[br]of heavily fortified trenches...

00:01:49.48,00:01:51.85
zigzagging their way 500 miles...

00:01:51.94,00:01:55.40
from the English Channel[br]to the Swiss frontier.

00:01:55.48,00:01:59.40
By 1916, after two grisly years[br]of trench warfare...

00:01:59.44,00:02:02.66
the battle lines had changed[br]very little.

00:02:02.74,00:02:06.28
Successful attacks were measured[br]in hundreds of yards...

00:02:06.37,00:02:09.41
and paid for in lives[br]by hundreds of thousands.

00:02:12.83,00:02:14.25
General Broulard, sir.

00:02:14.29,00:02:16.71
- Hello, George. How are you?[br]- Paul.

00:02:16.79,00:02:19.63
Wonderful seeing you again.[br]Really wonderful.

00:02:19.67,00:02:22.59
Well, this is splendid.

00:02:22.63,00:02:25.38
Superb! Grand, very grand.

00:02:25.47,00:02:28.09
Well, I've tried to create a pleasant[br]atmosphere in which to work.

00:02:28.18,00:02:32.47
You've succeeded marvellously. I wish I[br]had your taste in carpets and pictures.

00:02:32.56,00:02:35.73
You're much too kind, George.[br]Sit down, George.

00:02:35.81,00:02:37.73
- Thank you.[br]- I really haven't done very much.

00:02:37.81,00:02:41.23
The place is much the same[br]as it was when I moved in.

00:02:42.06,00:02:46.07
Paul, I've come to see you[br]about something big.

00:02:46.15,00:02:49.36
It's top secret and must go no further[br]than your chief of staff...

00:02:49.45,00:02:51.82
and not to him[br]unless you can trust his discretion.

00:02:51.86,00:02:53.12
Of course.

00:02:53.16,00:02:56.62
A group of armies is forming on this[br]front for an offensive very soon.

00:02:56.66,00:02:59.08
Headquarters is determined[br]to make a complete breakthrough.

00:02:59.16,00:03:01.46
- Why are you smiling?[br]- I'm really sorry.

00:03:01.50,00:03:04.96
I thought for a moment I knew what you[br]were going to say. Please go on.

00:03:05.00,00:03:07.46
What did you think[br]I was about to say?

00:03:09.05,00:03:11.76
- Something about the Ant Hill.[br]- You are a mind reader.

00:03:11.84,00:03:13.76
Well, it is a key position.

00:03:13.84,00:03:17.64
It's in my sector. To be perfectly[br]honest, I've heard some talk.

00:03:17.68,00:03:21.06
-There's nothing secret at headquarters.[br]-What do you think?

00:03:21.14,00:03:24.14
It's the key to the whole[br]German position in this sector.

00:03:24.22,00:03:26.18
They've held it for a year now...

00:03:26.27,00:03:28.73
and it looks as though they'll hold it[br]for another year if they want to.

00:03:28.81,00:03:31.44
I have formal orders to take[br]the Ant Hill no later than the tenth.

00:03:31.52,00:03:35.15
- That's the day after tomorrow.[br]- Don't you think that's ridiculous?

00:03:35.23,00:03:38.82
I don't imagine I'd be here[br]if I really thought that.

00:03:38.86,00:03:43.41
Paul, if there's one man in this army[br]who can do this for me, it's you.

00:03:44.16,00:03:47.45
It's out of the question.[br]Absolutely.

00:03:47.54,00:03:49.54
My division was cut to pieces.

00:03:49.62,00:03:53.17
What's left is in no position to even[br]hold the Ant Hill, let alone take it.

00:03:53.21,00:03:56.34
I'm sorry, but that's the truth.

00:03:56.42,00:03:59.67
Well, there was something else[br]I wanted to tell you...

00:03:59.76,00:04:02.84
however I'm sure you'll misunderstand[br]my motives in mentioning it.

00:04:02.88,00:04:07.55
- What was it?[br]- Oh, you'd be bound to misunderstand.

00:04:07.64,00:04:11.14
However, as your friend,[br]maybe I should tell you.

00:04:11.22,00:04:14.77
- What are you trying to say?[br]- Paul, the talk around headquarters...

00:04:14.85,00:04:17.65
is that you are being considered[br]for the 12th Corps.

00:04:17.73,00:04:20.48
- The 12th Corps?[br]- Yes, and with that, another star.

00:04:20.56,00:04:22.48
I've pushed it all I can.

00:04:22.57,00:04:25.78
The 12th Corps needs a fighting general,[br]and your star is overdue.

00:04:25.86,00:04:28.03
We both know that your record[br]is good enough...

00:04:28.07,00:04:30.86
for you to refuse this assignment[br]on the grounds you've stated.

00:04:30.91,00:04:35.45
No one would question your opinion.[br]They'd simply get someone else to do it.

00:04:35.54,00:04:39.54
So you shouldn't let this[br]influence your opinion.

00:04:41.21,00:04:44.21
- Oh, I'm sorry. Have a cognac?[br]- No, thanks. Not before dinner.

00:04:48.71,00:04:52.34
I am responsible for the lives[br]of 8,000 men.

00:04:53.43,00:04:56.14
What is my ambition against that?

00:04:56.22,00:04:59.51
What is my reputation[br]in comparison to that?

00:04:59.60,00:05:02.06
My men come first of all, George.

00:05:02.10,00:05:04.64
- And those men know it too.[br]- I know that.

00:05:04.73,00:05:07.81
You see, those men know[br]that I would never let them down.

00:05:07.90,00:05:09.56
That goes without saying.

00:05:09.61,00:05:14.19
One soldier's life means more to me[br]than all the decorations in France.

00:05:15.32,00:05:18.07
So, you think...

00:05:18.16,00:05:21.49
this attack is absolutely beyond[br]the ability of your men at this time?

00:05:21.57,00:05:24.91
I didn't say that, George.

00:05:24.95,00:05:28.58
Nothing is beyond those men[br]once their fighting spirit is aroused.

00:05:28.66,00:05:31.25
I don't want to push you[br]if you think it's ill-advised.

00:05:31.29,00:05:34.75
Don't worry. You couldn't do that[br]if you tried.

00:05:36.13,00:05:39.51
Of course, artillery[br]would make an enormous difference.

00:05:39.59,00:05:42.76
-What artillery support can you give me?[br]-Well, I'll see.

00:05:42.84,00:05:44.93
- What about replacements?[br]- We'll see what we can do...

00:05:44.97,00:05:48.22
but I feel sure that you can get along[br]with what you have.

00:05:48.31,00:05:50.22
We might just do it.

00:05:50.31,00:05:52.89
Paul, I knew that I was right[br]to come to you.

00:05:52.98,00:05:55.98
You are the man to take the Ant Hill.[br]As for that star--

00:05:56.06,00:05:58.15
That has nothing to do[br]with my decision!

00:05:58.23,00:06:00.15
If anything,[br]it would sway me the other way.

00:06:00.23,00:06:02.11
I realize that perfectly.

00:06:02.15,00:06:04.11
When do you see this coming off?

00:06:04.15,00:06:08.24
- No later than the day after tomorrow.[br]- We just might do it!

00:06:30.63,00:06:33.47
Hello there, soldier.[br]Ready to kill more Germans?

00:06:33.51,00:06:35.47
- Yes, sir.[br]- What's your name, soldier?

00:06:35.51,00:06:38.47
- Sir, Private Ferol, Company A.[br]- Aha. You married, Private?

00:06:38.52,00:06:41.27
- No, sir.[br]- I'll bet your mother's proud of you.

00:06:41.35,00:06:44.81
- Yes, sir.[br]- Carry on, Private, and good luck.

00:06:44.90,00:06:46.86
Thank you, sir.

00:06:51.36,00:06:53.32
- Morning, General.[br]- Good morning.

00:06:53.36,00:06:55.32
- Hello there, soldier.[br]- Sir.

00:06:55.36,00:06:57.49
- Ready to kill more Germans?[br]- Yes, sir.

00:06:57.57,00:06:59.53
Working over your rifle, I see.

00:06:59.57,00:07:02.12
That's the way.[br]The soldier's best friend.

00:07:02.20,00:07:04.41
You be good to it,[br]and it'll always be good to you.

00:07:04.50,00:07:06.41
Yes, sir.

00:07:09.17,00:07:11.17
Well, good luck to you, soldier.

00:07:11.21,00:07:13.17
- Carry on.[br]- Thank you, sir.

00:07:39.57,00:07:41.53
Hello there, soldier.

00:07:41.61,00:07:44.07
Ready to kill more Germans?

00:07:45.16,00:07:47.28
Is everything all right, soldier?

00:07:47.37,00:07:50.41
All right. Yes, sir.[br]I'm all right.

00:07:50.49,00:07:51.95
Good fella.

00:07:52.04,00:07:57.04
- Are you married, soldier?[br]- Married? Me, married?

00:07:57.08,00:08:00.67
- Yes. Have you got a wife?[br]- A wife? Have I got a wife?

00:08:00.75,00:08:02.96
Sir. He's a bit shellshocked.

00:08:03.05,00:08:08.38
I beg your pardon, Sergeant.[br]There is no such thing as shell shock.

00:08:08.42,00:08:09.88
Have you got a wife, soldier?

00:08:09.93,00:08:14.56
My wife? My wife. Yes, I have a wife.

00:08:14.60,00:08:16.56
I'm never gonna see her again.

00:08:16.60,00:08:19.10
Get a grip on yourself![br]You're acting like a coward!

00:08:19.14,00:08:21.60
- I am a coward, sir.[br]- Snap out of it!

00:08:21.69,00:08:25.77
Sergeant, I want you to immediately[br]transfer this baby out of my regiment!

00:08:25.86,00:08:28.53
I won't have other brave men[br]contaminated by him.

00:08:28.61,00:08:30.94
- Yes, sir.[br]- Carry on, Sergeant.

00:08:34.11,00:08:38.20
You were right, sir. This sort of thing[br]can spread if it isn't checked.

00:08:38.28,00:08:40.41
General, I'm convinced[br]that these tours of yours...

00:08:40.45,00:08:43.08
have an incalculable effect[br]upon the morale of these men.

00:08:43.12,00:08:46.08
I think the fighting spirit[br]of the 701st derives from it.

00:08:46.12,00:08:49.96
No, Major. That spirit[br]was just born in them.

00:08:55.55,00:08:57.80
The general is coming, sir.

00:09:12.44,00:09:15.27
- Always a pleasure to see you, Colonel.[br]- I'm honored, General.

00:09:15.32,00:09:17.32
It's our privilege entirely.

00:09:17.40,00:09:20.40
Well, quite a neat little spot[br]you have here.

00:09:20.49,00:09:24.20
I'll reserve comment on the neatness,[br]sir, but it is little.

00:09:24.28,00:09:26.57
Pretty shy[br]on seating accommodations, though.

00:09:26.66,00:09:29.95
More than enough for me.[br]Never got the habit of sitting.

00:09:29.99,00:09:32.75
Like to be on my feet,[br]keep on the move.

00:09:32.83,00:09:37.71
I can vouch for that. I can hardly[br]get him behind a desk to sign an order.

00:09:37.79,00:09:39.92
That's the way I am, you know, Dax.

00:09:40.00,00:09:42.92
I can't understand these[br]armchair officers--

00:09:43.01,00:09:47.09
fellows trying to fight from behind[br]a desk, waving papers at the enemy.

00:09:47.18,00:09:50.34
Worrying about whether a mouse is going[br]to run up their pants leg.

00:09:50.43,00:09:54.97
I don't know. If I could choose between[br]mice and Mausers, I'd take the mice.

00:09:55.02,00:09:57.10
You'll never make me believe that.

00:09:57.18,00:09:59.69
Seriously, though, if a man's a ninny...

00:09:59.77,00:10:02.40
let him put on a dress[br]and hide under the bed.

00:10:02.48,00:10:05.44
But if he wants to be a soldier,[br]then by heavens, he's got to be one.

00:10:05.52,00:10:09.65
He's got to fight. He can't do that[br]unless he's where the fighting is.

00:10:09.74,00:10:12.49
- That's my credo.[br]- I think I have to agree with you...

00:10:12.57,00:10:14.53
presenting your case[br]so convincingly, sir.

00:10:14.57,00:10:17.70
- You've never failed to live up to it.[br]- You'd like a look around?

00:10:17.78,00:10:19.49
Yes, Colonel.

00:10:19.58,00:10:22.33
Here's something to see.[br]The Ant Hill.

00:10:22.41,00:10:24.87
About as good a view as you can get[br]without actually being there.

00:10:24.96,00:10:27.71
Ha-ha. That won't be long now, will it?

00:10:30.71,00:10:32.46
Ah.

00:10:33.88,00:10:35.80
Yeah.

00:10:35.88,00:10:39.55
Well, I've seen much more formidable[br]objectives.

00:10:39.64,00:10:41.64
Much, much worse.

00:10:46.43,00:10:50.52
Well, not something[br]we can grab and run away with...

00:10:50.60,00:10:52.73
but certainly pregnable.

00:10:52.81,00:10:55.69
-Sounds kind of odd, though, doesn't it?[br]-Why?

00:10:55.73,00:10:58.03
Well, like something[br]to do with giving birth.

00:10:58.07,00:11:01.53
Oh, yes, quite. You're right on[br]your toes this morning, Colonel.

00:11:01.57,00:11:04.03
Even sharper than usual.[br]But we mustn't forget...

00:11:04.07,00:11:07.20
the colonel was perhaps the foremost[br]criminal lawyer in all France.

00:11:07.29,00:11:11.12
- Of course, General.[br]- Gentlemen, you're both much too kind.

00:11:11.21,00:11:14.54
Tell me, Colonel, how did your relief[br]come off last night?

00:11:14.58,00:11:17.63
We drew some artillery.[br]Twenty-nine casualties, sir.

00:11:17.71,00:11:21.76
Yes, I noticed it on the road in.[br]Utterly inexcusable. Stupid.

00:11:21.84,00:11:25.01
All swarmed together like flies,[br]just waiting for someone to swat them.

00:11:25.09,00:11:29.05
Well, they never learn, it seems. They[br]get in a tight spot under heavy fire--

00:11:29.14,00:11:31.72
gang up every time--[br]herd instinct, I suppose.

00:11:31.76,00:11:35.35
- Kind of a lower animal sort of thing.[br]- Kind of a human thing, it seems to me.

00:11:35.43,00:11:37.39
Don't you make a distinction between[br]the two, Major?

00:11:37.44,00:11:40.10
Oh, yes, very regrettable, of course.

00:11:40.19,00:11:44.69
Yes, indeed. Major, will you excuse us[br]for a few minutes?

00:11:44.78,00:11:46.86
Yes, sir. Of course.

00:11:47.94,00:11:49.36
Colonel.

00:11:53.95,00:11:56.62
Well, Colonel, what do you think of it?

00:11:56.70,00:11:59.62
- What do I think of what, sir?[br]- The Ant Hill.

00:11:59.70,00:12:04.63
Colonel, your regiment is going to[br]take the Ant Hill tomorrow.

00:12:04.71,00:12:08.42
- You know the condition of my men, sir.[br]- Naturally, men are gonna be killed.

00:12:08.46,00:12:11.88
Possibly a lot of them.[br]They'll absorb bullets and shrapnel...

00:12:11.97,00:12:14.30
and by doing so make it possible[br]for others to get through.

00:12:14.38,00:12:17.64
- What support will we have?[br]- I have none to give you.

00:12:18.97,00:12:21.47
What sort of casualties[br]do you anticipate, sir?

00:12:21.56,00:12:26.27
Say, five percent killed by our own[br]barrage. That's a generous allowance.

00:12:26.35,00:12:28.73
Ten percent more in getting through[br]no-man's-land...

00:12:28.81,00:12:31.06
and 20 percent more[br]getting through the wire.

00:12:31.15,00:12:35.03
That leaves 65 percent[br]with the worst part of the job over.

00:12:35.11,00:12:39.11
Let's say another 25 percent[br]in actually taking the Ant Hill.

00:12:39.16,00:12:42.20
We're still left with a force[br]more than adequate to hold it.

00:12:42.28,00:12:45.16
General, you're saying that[br]more than half my men will be killed.

00:12:45.24,00:12:48.00
Yes, it's a terrible price to pay,[br]Colonel.

00:12:48.08,00:12:52.50
- But we will have the Ant Hill.[br]- But will we, sir?

00:12:52.54,00:12:57.13
I'm depending on you, Colonel.[br]All France is depending on you.

00:13:00.21,00:13:02.17
Am I amusing you, Colonel?

00:13:03.51,00:13:06.85
I'm not a bull, General. I don't need[br]a flag waved to get me to charge.

00:13:06.93,00:13:09.89
I don't like your comparison of the flag[br]of France to a bullfighter's cape.

00:13:09.97,00:13:12.14
I meant nothing disrespectful[br]to the flag of France, sir.

00:13:12.18,00:13:15.73
Patriotism may be old-fashioned,[br]but a patriot is an honest man.

00:13:15.81,00:13:19.56
Not everyone has always thought so.[br]Samuel Johnson said something else.

00:13:19.65,00:13:21.07
What was that?

00:13:22.86,00:13:25.07
- Nothing, really.[br]- What do you mean, "Nothing, really"?

00:13:25.15,00:13:28.53
- Well, sir, nothing really important.[br]- When I ask a question, it's important.

00:13:28.61,00:13:31.16
- Now, who was this man?[br]- Samuel Johnson, sir.

00:13:31.24,00:13:33.95
All right. What did he have to say[br]about patriotism?

00:13:34.04,00:13:37.25
He said it was the last refuge[br]of a scoundrel, sir. I'm sorry.

00:13:37.33,00:13:39.33
I meant nothing personal.

00:13:39.41,00:13:42.67
You're tired, Dax.[br]You're very tired.

00:13:42.71,00:13:46.17
It's you who are exhausted,[br]not your men, and it's my fault.

00:13:46.21,00:13:49.97
I've given you one impossible task[br]after another. You need rest badly.

00:13:50.05,00:13:52.30
- I haven't said that![br]- And you never would, either.

00:13:52.38,00:13:54.51
Therefore you're not going to have[br]any say-so about it, Colonel.

00:13:54.59,00:13:57.30
I'm ordering you on indefinite furlough.

00:13:57.39,00:13:59.97
General, you can't take me away from[br]my men. You can't do that to me, sir!

00:14:00.06,00:14:03.69
Not to you, Dax. For you. For your good[br]and for the good of your men.

00:14:03.73,00:14:05.69
The good of my men, sir?

00:14:05.73,00:14:09.52
If an officer lacks confidence,[br]what can we expect of his men?

00:14:09.57,00:14:13.69
Naturally, I don't want to relieve you,[br]but I must have enthusiastic support.

00:14:13.78,00:14:18.03
Not once have you said that your men[br]can take the Ant Hill.

00:14:19.28,00:14:23.04
We'll take the Ant Hill.

00:14:23.08,00:14:26.50
If any soldiers in the world[br]can take it...

00:14:26.58,00:14:28.92
we'll take the Ant Hill.

00:14:29.00,00:14:32.33
And when you do, your men will be[br]relieved and get a long rest.

00:14:48.10,00:14:50.31
Corporal Paris and Private Lejeune[br]reporting, sir.

00:14:51.14,00:14:52.60
You took your time.

00:14:52.64,00:14:56.56
We prepared as quick as we could, sir.[br]We had to alert the sentries.

00:14:56.61,00:15:00.32
All right. You men, at ease.[br]This is a reconnaissance patrol.

00:15:00.40,00:15:04.24
German wire, machine gun posts,[br]identification of bodies.

00:15:04.28,00:15:07.70
There'll only be the three of us,[br]and we're to avoid a fight if we can.

00:15:09.74,00:15:14.08
We go out to the left, and we come back[br]through Post Six on the right.

00:15:14.12,00:15:16.87
- Is everything all clear at Post Six?[br]- All the sentries have been warned.

00:15:16.96,00:15:20.33
Number six will send up flares at[br]ten minute intervals starting at 0400.

00:15:20.42,00:15:23.29
- I wanted them every five minutes.[br]- I told them that, sir.

00:15:23.34,00:15:26.71
The sergeant says every five minutes[br]is too much. It'll draw artillery.

00:15:26.80,00:15:28.84
Quite a strategist, this sergeant.[br]What's his name?

00:15:28.92,00:15:31.30
I don't know, sir.

00:15:32.89,00:15:35.64
All right. You men wait outside.[br]I'll join you in a minute.

00:15:35.72,00:15:38.27
Would you mind telling us[br]the password, sir?

00:15:38.35,00:15:40.81
- Calais.[br]- Yes, sir.

00:15:49.23,00:15:52.65
- He's fortifying himself.[br]- It smelled like heaven.

00:15:52.69,00:15:55.78
I can always tell when he's had a few.[br]He gets sarcastic.

00:15:55.82,00:15:58.74
Well, at least[br]he could have passed it around, the pig.

00:15:58.82,00:16:01.87
Hey, what's he got against you anyway?

