00:21:39.91,00:21:42.37
I don't think I like your tone.

00:21:42.45,00:21:44.70
You're speaking to an officer.[br]Remember that.

00:21:44.79,00:21:48.00
Oh, well, I must be mistaken, then, sir.

00:21:48.08,00:21:50.58
An officer wouldn't do that.

00:21:50.67,00:21:53.08
A man wouldn't do it.

00:21:53.13,00:21:55.09
Only a thing would.

00:21:55.13,00:21:57.09
A sneaky, booze-guzzling...

00:21:57.13,00:22:00.76
yellow-bellied rat[br]with a bottle for a brain...

00:22:00.84,00:22:03.47
- That's enough.[br]- and a streak of spit for a spine.

00:22:03.55,00:22:06.76
- You got yourself into a mess.[br]- Oh, I have?

00:22:06.80,00:22:10.35
Well, you've got yourself in a worse[br]one. First, general insubordination.

00:22:10.43,00:22:13.44
Second, threatening[br]your superior officer.

00:22:13.52,00:22:17.81
Third, refusing to obey an order[br]and inciting others to do the same.

00:22:17.90,00:22:20.44
How do you think those charges[br]are going to look on paper?

00:22:20.52,00:22:22.73
Not half as bad as these.

00:22:22.82,00:22:25.78
Endangering the lives of your men[br]through recklessness...

00:22:25.86,00:22:29.87
drunk on duty, wanton murder[br]of one of your own men...

00:22:29.95,00:22:33.04
and cowardice in the face[br]of the enemy.

00:22:34.70,00:22:39.58
