00:23:18.03,00:23:20.83
- Oh, good morning, Colonel.[br]- At ease, men.

00:23:20.87,00:23:24.45
- I've been waiting for your report.[br]- We found out a thing or two.

00:23:24.54,00:23:28.25
- Everything go well?[br]- No, sir. Private Lejeune was killed.

00:23:28.33,00:23:30.46
- How'd it happen?[br]- It's in the report, sir.

00:23:30.54,00:23:33.67
- Let's have it.[br]- It isn't quite finished yet, sir.

00:23:33.71,00:23:35.80
That's all, Corporal.[br]You did a good night's work.

00:23:35.88,00:23:39.17
Should feel very proud of yourself.[br]Go get some sleep.

00:23:39.22,00:23:40.68
Yes, sir.

00:23:45.14,00:23:48.35
- How'd you lose Lejeune?[br]- Machine gun fire, sir.

00:23:48.43,00:23:52.39
He coughed. Almost got us all killed.

00:23:52.44,00:23:54.77
Finish that report and get it[br]to my dugout immediately.

00:23:54.85,00:23:56.27
Yes, sir.

00:24:01.28,00:24:05.03
The artillery starts at 0515.

00:24:05.11,00:24:09.12
The First Battalion[br]will move out at 0530.

00:24:09.20,00:24:11.37
When the leading elements[br]have cleared the German wires...

00:24:11.45,00:24:14.25
the second wave, consisting of[br]the Second and Third Battalions...

00:24:14.33,00:24:17.75
minus two companies in reserve,[br]will move out.

00:24:17.83,00:24:21.79
In no case later than 0540.

00:24:21.88,00:24:24.67
That's it, gentlemen.[br]Are there any questions?

