00:24:37.10,00:24:38.02
Too good.

00:24:39.35,00:24:42.06
No chance of rain or fog?

00:24:42.10,00:24:44.61
The forecast is for sun all day.

00:24:44.65,00:24:49.07
If, or perhaps I should say when,[br]we take the Ant Hill...

00:24:49.11,00:24:52.11
how long do we have to hold it[br]before we can expect any support?

00:24:52.99,00:24:56.57
General Mireau, who, by the way, will be[br]personally observing the attack...

00:24:56.66,00:24:59.53
has promised support from the 72nd[br]by sundown tomorrow...

00:24:59.62,00:25:03.79
which means, of course,[br]that we'll have to hold all day.

00:25:04.71,00:25:06.29
Any more questions?

00:25:10.04,00:25:14.26
Well, gentlemen, good luck. I'm sure[br]you'll come through as you always do.

00:25:14.30,00:25:16.01
Let's get some sleep.

00:25:18.13,00:25:21.26
I'm not afraid of dying tomorrow,[br]only of getting killed.

00:25:21.30,00:25:24.26
- That's as clear as mud.[br]- Which would you rather be done in by?

00:25:24.31,00:25:27.02
- A bayonet or a machine gun?[br]- Machine gun, naturally.

00:25:27.10,00:25:30.85
That's my point. They're both pieces[br]of steel ripping into your guts...

00:25:30.94,00:25:33.73
only the machine gun is quicker,[br]cleaner and less painful, isn't it?

00:25:33.81,00:25:35.61
- What does that prove?[br]- That proves most of us...

00:25:35.69,00:25:38.86
are more afraid of getting hurt[br]than getting killed.

00:25:38.94,00:25:43.28
Look at Bernard. He panics when it comes[br]to gas. Gas doesn't bother me a bit.

00:25:43.32,00:25:46.91
He's seen photos of gas cases,[br]but it doesn't mean anything to me.

00:25:46.99,00:25:50.33
But I'll tell you something. I'd hate[br]like the devil to be without my tin hat.

00:25:50.37,00:25:52.96
But I don't mind not having a tin hat[br]for my tail.

00:25:53.04,00:25:55.42
- Why's that?[br]- That's where your brains are.

00:25:55.50,00:25:57.92
