00:25:58.00,00:26:01.05
The tail is just meat, but the head--[br]the head is all bone.

00:26:01.13,00:26:03.46
- Speak for yourself.[br]- Tell me this.

00:26:03.51,00:26:06.05
Aside from the bayonet,[br]what are you most afraid of?

00:26:06.13,00:26:08.38
- High explosives.[br]- Exactly. It's the same with me.

00:26:08.47,00:26:11.39
Because I know that it can chew you up[br]worse than anything else.

00:26:11.47,00:26:14.06
Look, it's like I'm trying to tell you.[br]If you're really afraid of dying...

00:26:14.14,00:26:16.14
you'd be living in a funk[br]all the rest of your life...

00:26:16.22,00:26:18.48
because you know you've got to go[br]someday, any day.

00:26:18.52,00:26:23.02
If death is what you really fear, why[br]should you care about what kills you?

00:26:23.11,00:26:27.65
You're too smart for me, Professor.[br]All I know is nobody wants to die.

00:26:36.74,00:26:39.49
Through to Division, sir.[br]Through to Polygon.

00:26:39.54,00:26:43.46
Everything quiet.[br]All units report themselves ready.

00:26:43.54,00:26:46.17
Zero minus two.

00:26:46.21,00:26:48.17
May I offer you gentlemen[br]some cognac?

00:26:48.21,00:26:49.67
Thank you, sir.

00:26:53.46,00:26:55.38
After you, sir.

00:26:57.09,00:26:58.55
To France.

00:28:39.97,00:28:44.43
Minus 15, 14, 13...

00:28:46.44,00:28:49.65
ten, nine, eight...

00:28:49.73,00:28:53.53
seven, six, five, four...

00:28:53.61,00:28:56.90
three, two, one, zero.

00:31:55.05,00:31:56.72
Sergeant, where's B Company?

00:31:56.81,00:31:58.72
I don't know, sir.

00:32:02.98,00:32:05.61
- Where in heaven's name are they?[br]- On the left, sir.

00:32:05.65,00:32:08.77
Where are the rest? Zero plus one,[br]and they're still in the trenches.

00:32:08.82,00:32:12.61
They're not advancing. Miserable[br]cowards! They're not advancing!

00:32:12.65,00:32:15.66
The barrage is getting away from them.[br]They're still in the trenches!

00:32:15.74,00:32:17.16
Yes, sir.

00:32:19.03,00:32:20.16
Captain Nichols.

00:32:20.24,00:32:21.70
Yes, sir?

00:32:22.83,00:32:25.62
Order the 75's to commence[br]firing on our own positions.

00:32:27.12,00:32:31.59
Captain, do you fail to comprehend[br]the meaning of my order?

00:32:31.67,00:32:34.05
No, sir, but I respectfully[br]ask to--

00:32:34.13,00:32:37.38
Captain, do you fail to comprehend[br]the meaning of my order?

00:32:37.47,00:32:38.38
No, sir.

00:32:38.47,00:32:41.43
- Then carry it out, Captain.[br]- Yes, sir.

00:32:46.64,00:32:51.27
Hello, Polygon?[br]This is Division.

00:32:51.35,00:32:54.27
Batteries One and Two commence firing...

00:32:54.36,00:32:59.32
on coordinates 32-58-78.

00:32:59.40,00:33:01.99
Batteries One and Two[br]to commence firing...

00:33:02.07,00:33:07.12
on coordinates 32-58-78, over.

00:33:15.29,00:33:18.63
General, the battery commander[br]reports those are our own positions.

00:33:18.71,00:33:20.29
He says it must be a mistake.

00:33:20.38,00:33:23.13
- Confirm the order, Captain.[br]- Yes, sir.

00:33:23.21,00:33:25.63
There is no mistake.[br]The order is confirmed.

00:33:25.72,00:33:29.59
Battery commander respectfully reports[br]he cannot execute such an order...

00:33:29.68,00:33:33.35
unless it is in writing and signed[br]by the general, over.

00:33:33.39,00:33:37.64
General, battery commander reports[br]he cannot execute such an order...

00:33:37.73,00:33:39.89
unless it is in writing and signed[br]by the general.

00:33:39.98,00:33:42.02
- Give me that phone.[br]- Yes, sir.

00:33:46.61,00:33:47.94
General Mireau speaking.

00:33:48.03,00:33:49.82
Battery commander speaking, sir.

00:33:49.90,00:33:54.32
The troops are mutinying, refusing[br]to advance. Fire until further notice!

00:33:54.41,00:33:58.24
With all respect, sir, you have no right[br]to order me to shoot down my own men...

00:33:58.33,00:34:01.87
unless you are willing to take full[br]and undivided responsibility for it.

00:34:01.91,00:34:04.41
Captain Rousseau, are you going[br]to obey my order?

00:34:04.46,00:34:08.08
I must have a written order before[br]I can execute such a command, sir.

00:34:08.17,00:34:10.54
Supposing you are killed?[br]Then where will I be?

00:34:10.59,00:34:14.13
You'll be in front of a firing squad[br]tomorrow morning!

00:34:14.21,00:34:18.68
Hand over your command. Report yourself[br]under arrest to my headquarters!

00:34:29.81,00:34:32.48
Roget!

00:34:32.56,00:34:36.82
- Why are your men still in here?[br]- Impossible, sir. Major Vignon is dead.

00:34:36.90,00:34:39.07
Get these men out of the trenches!

00:34:39.11,00:34:44.03
Come on! Let's get ready for another[br]try! Get these men out of here!

00:34:44.12,00:34:46.37
I've tried three times![br]Look at all the casualties.

00:34:46.45,00:34:51.20
All right, let's give it another try![br]Come on!

00:35:02.30,00:35:05.76
It's impossible, sir.[br]All the men are falling back.

00:35:06.97,00:35:11.39
Sir, I respectfully submit[br]to the colonel.

00:35:11.47,00:35:16.10
Pardon. Your remarks to me[br]were very unfair, sir.

00:35:16.14,00:35:19.85
It's just impossible.

00:35:19.94,00:35:23.61
General, according to first reports, the[br]attack has failed all along the line.

00:35:23.69,00:35:26.28
The men are falling back[br]to our own trenches.

00:35:26.36,00:35:31.16
Major Saint-Auban, arrange for the[br]immediate relief of the 701st Regiment.

