00:37:06.94,00:37:09.91
My only aim is to remind you[br]of the heroism these men have shown...

00:37:09.99,00:37:12.03
on every occasion in the past.

00:37:12.12,00:37:15.04
We're not talking about the past.[br]We're talking about the present.

00:37:15.08,00:37:17.58
But don't you see, sir?[br]They're not cowards.

00:37:17.66,00:37:20.83
If some didn't leave the trenches,[br]it must have been impossible.

00:37:20.92,00:37:25.46
They were ordered to attack.[br]It was their duty to obey that order.

00:37:25.54,00:37:28.42
We can't leave it up to the men[br]to decide whether an order is possible.

00:37:28.50,00:37:32.59
If it was impossible, the only proof[br]of that would be their dead bodies...

00:37:32.68,00:37:35.09
lying in the trenches.

00:37:35.18,00:37:37.22
They're scum, Colonel.

00:37:37.26,00:37:41.89
The whole rotten regiment is a pack of[br]sneaking, whining, tail-dragging curs.

00:37:41.97,00:37:43.43
Do you really believe that?

00:37:43.48,00:37:46.77
Yes, I do.[br]That's exactly what I believe.

00:37:46.85,00:37:49.81
And what's more,[br]it's an incontestable fact.

00:37:49.90,00:37:53.07
Why not shoot the entire regiment?[br]I'm perfectly serious.

00:37:53.11,00:37:57.57
You're missing the point entirely. We[br]don't want to slaughter the French army.

00:37:57.65,00:37:59.61
All we want[br]is to set an example.

00:37:59.66,00:38:01.99
Oh, if it's an example you want,[br]then take me.

00:38:02.08,00:38:04.49
- Take you?[br]- Yes, sir. If you want an example...

00:38:04.58,00:38:06.20
one man will do as well as a hundred.

00:38:06.29,00:38:10.75
The logical choice is the officer[br]most responsible for the attack.

00:38:12.13,00:38:13.92
Come, Colonel.[br]I think you're overwrought.

00:38:14.00,00:38:16.63
This is not a question of officers.

00:38:16.71,00:38:19.84
Paul, we don't want to overdo[br]this thing.

00:38:19.92,00:38:21.55
Suppose we just make it a dozen.

00:38:22.84,00:38:25.72
I was talking of a hundred men.[br]Now we're down to 12.

00:38:25.80,00:38:28.18
Paul, let's not haggle over this[br]anymore.

00:38:28.26,00:38:31.31
Let's get it settled once and for all,[br]so we can all live with it.

00:38:33.56,00:38:38.48
Well, perhaps I was a bit too anxious[br]to see proper justice meted out.

00:38:38.52,00:38:40.61
I've spent my entire life in the army.

00:38:40.69,00:38:43.11
I've always tried to be true[br]to my principles.

00:38:43.15,00:38:47.11
It's the only mistake[br]I can ever be accused of.

00:38:47.16,00:38:49.28
I'll settle for this:

00:38:49.37,00:38:53.95
Have the company commanders select one[br]man from each company in the first wave.

00:38:54.04,00:38:57.00
- Three in all.[br]- Well, that's very reasonable, Paul.

00:38:57.04,00:39:00.88
The court martial will meet[br]at the chateau at 3:00 this afternoon.

00:39:00.96,00:39:03.59
- Will that be convenient for you?[br]- I won't be there, Paul.

00:39:03.67,00:39:05.05
You won't be there?

00:39:05.13,00:39:07.55
No. I think it best that you handle[br]this matter on your own.

00:39:07.63,00:39:09.59
Probably so.

00:39:09.67,00:39:13.14
General Mireau, if it's possible...

00:39:13.22,00:39:15.47
I'd like to be appointed counsel[br]for the accused.

00:39:15.55,00:39:17.26
I'll take it under consideration.

00:39:17.35,00:39:20.22
Oh, we can permit that.[br]Consider it settled, Colonel.

00:39:20.31,00:39:21.31
Thank you, sir.

00:39:24.35,00:39:27.02
Noon straight up, Paul. I hope that[br]you can stay for lunch, Colonel.

00:39:27.11,00:39:30.15
George, I'm afraid the colonel[br]won't have time.

