Keeping him for your own.[br]I think that was very selfish of you.

00:39:35.70,00:39:39.91
Thank you, General, but I'm afraid there[br]isn't much time between now and 3:00.

00:39:39.99,00:39:43.91
Of course, Colonel. I shall look forward[br]to the pleasure of seeing you again.

00:40:03.85,00:40:06.64
- Yes, Captain? What is it?[br]- You ordered me to report to you, sir.

00:40:06.72,00:40:09.77
- Captain Rousseau, Battery Commander.[br]- Yes, of course.

00:40:09.85,00:40:13.69
I wanted to speak to you about[br]some of your shells falling short.

00:40:13.73,00:40:17.98
I haven't time now. Report back[br]to your command until further orders.

00:40:18.07,00:40:19.48
Yes, sir.

00:40:21.82,00:40:25.11
- Bad stuff. It demoralizes the men.[br]- I quite agree with you.

00:40:25.20,00:40:27.87
The best solution is to shelve him[br]to another outfit.

00:40:27.91,00:40:29.99
A court of inquiry ought to roast him[br]a bit first.

00:40:30.08,00:40:34.54
Well, in cases like shells falling[br]short, I always try to avoid an inquiry.

00:40:34.62,00:40:38.08
It gets around among the men[br]and makes a bad impression.

00:40:38.12,00:40:40.42
Shelving will be the best discipline[br]for him in my opinion.

00:40:40.50,00:40:43.46
- Perhaps you're right.[br]- Oh, would you excuse me for a moment?

00:40:43.55,00:40:45.46
A regimental matter for the colonel.

00:40:45.55,00:40:47.88
- I'll join you in the dining room.[br]- Splendid. In a moment.

00:40:49.72,00:40:52.51
There'll be Captain Sancy,[br]Captain Renouart and Lieutenant Roget.

00:40:52.60,00:40:55.43
- Yes, sir.[br]- Have them meet me in half an hour.

00:40:55.51,00:40:57.43
- Yes, sir.[br]- Colonel Dax?

00:40:58.73,00:41:01.35
- Yes, sir.[br]- I'd like a word.

00:41:01.44,00:41:03.77
Certainly, sir.

00:41:03.85,00:41:08.44
- Let's be sensible about this.[br]- Sensible, sir?

00:41:08.53,00:41:13.45
Listen to me, Dax. You can cut out[br]this fancy talk with me, understand?

00:41:13.53,00:41:17.37
General Broulard seemed to think[br]you're funny. I don't.

00:41:17.45,00:41:21.66
- I want you to drop this affair.[br]- I beg your pardon. Is that an order?

00:41:21.74,00:41:25.54
Colonel Dax, when this mess[br]is cleaned up, I'll break you!

00:41:25.62,00:41:27.58
I'll find an excuse,[br]and I'll break you to the ranks.

00:41:27.67,00:41:30.54
I'll ruin you. It will be[br]just what you deserve...

00:41:30.63,00:41:34.17
showing such little loyalty[br]to your commanding officer.

00:41:34.26,00:41:36.30
That's all, Colonel.

00:41:59.11,00:42:02.20
General Mireau feels that the attack[br]on the Ant Hill yesterday morning...

00:42:02.28,00:42:05.95
failed because of an inadequate effort[br]on the part of the First Battalion.

00:42:06.03,00:42:08.45
Each of you is to select one man[br]from your company...

00:42:08.49,00:42:12.25
place him under arrest and have him[br]appear before a general court martial...

00:42:12.33,00:42:15.00
no later than 1500 hours this afternoon.

00:42:15.08,00:42:17.42
The charge is cowardice[br]in the face of the enemy.

00:42:17.50,00:42:20.46
You have your orders, gentlemen.[br]Let's carry them out.

00:42:40.35,00:42:42.81
But Lieutenant Roget killed Lejeune[br]on that patrol...

00:42:42.86,00:42:45.27
and then blackmailed me[br]into keeping quiet about it!

00:42:45.36,00:42:47.90
- That's why he picked me![br]- Corporal, I understand your feelings.

00:42:47.98,00:42:50.65
But that has nothing to do with[br]the charges you're being tried for.

00:42:50.74,00:42:53.61
- Don't you believe me, sir?[br]- Yes, I do.

00:42:53.70,00:42:57.33
But who else will?[br]You've got no witnesses.

00:42:57.41,00:43:01.33
Besides, such charges against an officer[br]would only antagonize the court.

00:43:01.37,00:43:04.92
When we get clear of this, I'm going[br]into the story of that patrol again.

00:43:05.00,00:43:08.88
Sir, in my case, Captain Renouart[br]had the sergeant draw lots.

00:43:08.96,00:43:11.09
I was picked purely by chance.

00:43:11.17,00:43:13.63
You were lucky. Look at me.

00:43:13.72,00:43:18.18
I was just picked because Captain Sancy[br]said I was a social undesirable.

00:43:18.26,00:43:20.51
Me, a social undesirable.

00:43:20.60,00:43:23.22
I didn't act like a coward.[br]Picking by lots! Is that fair?

00:43:23.31,00:43:24.43
Gentlemen!

00:43:24.52,00:43:27.23
You've all got to understand that the[br]reason you were picked is immaterial.

00:43:27.31,00:43:31.31
Whatever the reason,[br]you're on trial for your lives.

00:43:35.02,00:43:39.95
Stick to your stories, and don't let[br]the prosecutor shake you out of them.

00:43:40.03,00:43:43.49
Now remember, you'll be soldiers[br]in the presence of superior officers...

00:43:43.57,00:43:45.53
so act like what you are.

00:43:45.58,00:43:47.37
Soldiers.

00:43:47.45,00:43:49.95
And brave ones at that.

00:43:50.04,00:43:53.42
I've been in the room you'll be sitting[br]in. The sun will be in your faces...

00:43:53.50,00:43:57.84
so don't let it seem as if you're[br]dropping your eyes in a hangdog manner.

00:43:59.17,00:44:01.51
When you answer questions,[br]look the judges in the eye.

00:44:01.59,00:44:04.51
Don't whine, plead or make speeches.[br]That's my job.

00:44:04.59,00:44:06.55
Simple statements. Short.

00:44:06.64,00:44:08.64
But make them so they can be heard[br]all over the room.

00:44:08.72,00:44:12.68
And try not to repeat yourselves.[br]I'll do that for you when I sum up.

00:44:12.77,00:44:15.23
We haven't much time. The court martial[br]begins in about an hour.

00:44:15.27,00:44:17.23
I've got notes to look at.

00:44:19.15,00:44:21.36
Good luck.

00:44:21.44,00:44:23.36
Thank you, Colonel.

00:45:04.06,00:45:07.02
The court martial is opened.[br]Prisoners may be seated.

00:45:13.98,00:45:18.28
This is a general court martial. We'll[br]dispense with unnecessary formalities.

00:45:19.36,00:45:22.95
These men are charged with cowardice[br]in the face of the enemy...

00:45:23.03,00:45:25.49
and will be tried for that offense.

00:45:25.54,00:45:26.79
Mr. Prosecutor.

00:45:26.87,00:45:30.12
Call the accused, Private Ferol.

00:45:30.21,00:45:33.29
Mr. President, will the prosecutor...

00:45:33.38,00:45:36.13
question the witnesses[br]without even reading the indictment?

00:45:36.21,00:45:39.80
Please don't take up the court's time[br]with technicalities.

00:45:39.84,00:45:43.63
The indictment is lengthy[br]and there's no point in reading it.

00:45:43.72,00:45:46.30
- The defense has a right--[br]- The indictment is...

00:45:46.34,00:45:48.97
that the accused showed cowardice[br]in the face of the enemy...

00:45:49.06,00:45:51.22
during the attack on the Ant Hill.

00:45:51.31,00:45:54.27
Proceed, Mr. Prosecutor.

00:45:54.35,00:45:57.10
Call the accused, Private Ferol.

00:46:06.99,00:46:09.95
- Private Ferol.[br]- Yes, sir?

00:46:10.03,00:46:13.08
Were you in the first wave[br]during the attack on the Ant Hill?

00:46:13.16,00:46:16.33
- Yes, sir.[br]- Did you refuse to advance?

00:46:16.41,00:46:18.37
No, sir.

00:46:18.46,00:46:21.54
- Did you advance?[br]- Yes, sir.

00:46:21.62,00:46:23.17
How far did you advance?

00:46:23.25,00:46:27.50
- To about the middle of no-man's-land.[br]- Then what did you do?

00:46:27.59,00:46:30.92
There were machine gun bullets[br]landing all around--

00:46:31.01,00:46:33.59
Answer the question.[br]What did you do?

00:46:33.68,00:46:38.06
Well, I saw that me and Meyer--

00:46:38.10,00:46:40.27
I didn't ask what you saw.

00:46:40.35,00:46:44.35
The court has no concern[br]with your visual experiences.

00:46:44.44,00:46:47.77
- My what, sir?[br]- You will reply to the question.

00:46:47.86,00:46:49.57
Yes, sir. What question was it?

00:46:49.65,00:46:53.57
You advanced to the middle of[br]no-man's-land. What did you do then?

00:46:53.65,00:46:56.36
- Then, sir?[br]- Did you go back or forward?

00:46:56.40,00:47:00.41
- I went back, sir.[br]- In other words, Private Ferol...

00:47:01.66,00:47:03.08
you retreated.

00:47:04.24,00:47:05.66
Yes, sir.

00:47:05.75,00:47:09.37
That's all. The accused[br]may return to his seat.

00:47:09.46,00:47:10.71
Just a minute.

00:47:11.79,00:47:15.42
Mr. President, I'd like to question[br]the witness, if I may.

00:47:15.50,00:47:17.17
Proceed, Colonel.

00:47:17.26,00:47:22.05
Thank you. Private Ferol, when you[br]reached the middle of no-man's-land...

00:47:22.09,00:47:24.09
were you alone with Private Meyer?

00:47:24.14,00:47:25.35
Yes, sir.

00:47:25.43,00:47:27.64
What happened to the rest[br]of your company?

00:47:27.72,00:47:32.14
Well, I don't know, sir. I guess the[br]rest of them had been killed or wounded.

00:47:32.23,00:47:36.19
You found yourself in the middle of[br]no-man's-land alone with Private Meyer?

00:47:36.27,00:47:39.48
- Yes, sir.[br]- Why didn't you attack single-handed?

00:47:43.74,00:47:46.57
Why didn't you storm the Ant Hill alone?

00:47:46.66,00:47:48.87
Just me and Meyer? You're kidding, sir.

00:47:50.33,00:47:54.20
Yes, I'm kidding, Private Ferol.[br]Thank you. That's all.

00:47:54.29,00:47:57.00
I don't see the point of this line[br]of questioning.

00:47:57.08,00:48:00.46
Well, I'm attempting to indicate, sir,[br]the utter absurdity...

00:48:00.54,00:48:04.09
of the line of questioning[br]used by the prosecutor.

00:48:04.13,00:48:05.55
Mr. Prosecutor.

00:48:05.63,00:48:10.05
So you freely admit, Private Ferol,[br]that you retreated?

00:48:10.13,00:48:12.89
Yes, sir. Me and Meyer both.

00:48:12.97,00:48:17.10
I knew we should have took Ant Hill,[br]but we came on back.

00:48:19.14,00:48:21.44
That's all.

00:48:23.23,00:48:25.73
The accused may return to his seat.

00:48:35.49,00:48:39.20
Private Arnaud, did you advance?

00:48:39.28,00:48:44.04
Yes, sir, until I was ordered back[br]to the trenches by Captain Renouart.

00:48:44.12,00:48:46.21
How far did you advance?

00:48:46.29,00:48:48.21
Into the wire, sir.

00:48:48.29,00:48:52.09
The enemy wire, I suppose.

00:48:52.17,00:48:54.09
No, sir. It was our wire.

00:48:55.55,00:49:00.89
You mean to tell me that you didn't[br]advance any further than our wire?

00:49:00.97,00:49:02.93
No, sir. I didn't.

00:49:04.14,00:49:07.64
How far would you say that was?[br]How many meters?

00:49:07.72,00:49:10.39
Well, I advanced as far as I could.

00:49:10.48,00:49:12.65
How many meters?

00:49:13.81,00:49:14.90
Not many.

00:49:16.94,00:49:18.86
Not many?

00:49:21.49,00:49:23.49
Now, Private Arnaud...

00:49:23.57,00:49:26.99
before you were ordered back...

00:49:27.03,00:49:29.41
did you urge your fellow soldiers[br]forward?

00:49:31.12,00:49:34.41
Most were dead or wounded before they[br]got three steps beyond the trenches.

00:49:34.50,00:49:35.83
Reply to the question.

00:49:35.92,00:49:38.50
I didn't urge them on.[br]No, sir.

00:49:42.21,00:49:43.67
Thank you.

00:49:49.68,00:49:53.97
Private Arnaud, at ease, please.

00:49:55.89,00:50:00.19
Aside from your sad failure to give[br]throat to spirited battle cries...

00:50:00.23,00:50:02.23
was your behavior different[br]in any respect...

00:50:02.27,00:50:04.15
from that of the other men?

00:50:04.23,00:50:06.02
Objection.[br]That's a matter of conjecture.

00:50:06.11,00:50:08.32
Sustained.

00:50:11.40,00:50:14.20
Did any men in your company[br]get beyond our wire?

00:50:14.28,00:50:15.66
No, sir.

00:50:15.74,00:50:18.12
Is it true that you've been designated[br]a coward...

00:50:18.20,00:50:20.83
simply and purely because you drew[br]a slip of paper marked "X"?

00:50:20.91,00:50:21.83
Yes, sir.

00:50:21.91,00:50:24.00
I don't see that that's significant.

00:50:24.08,00:50:27.88
It's accepted practice in the French[br]army to pick examples by lot.

00:50:27.96,00:50:30.50
Since this entire company advanced[br]only a few meters...

00:50:30.59,00:50:33.55
picking by lot was eminently fair[br]in this case.

00:50:33.59,00:50:36.38
Well, I'd like to point out that this[br]soldier has distinguished himself...

00:50:36.47,00:50:39.84
in some of the bloodiest battles[br]of the war.

00:50:39.93,00:50:42.97
With the court's permission,[br]I'll read citations for bravery...

00:50:43.06,00:50:46.39
that he's already earned on[br]two occasions.

00:50:46.48,00:50:50.23
First, citations[br]in the Orders in the Army for bravery--

00:50:50.27,00:50:53.73
That's immaterial. The accused is not[br]being tried for his former bravery...

00:50:53.81,00:50:55.82
but for his recent cowardice.

00:50:55.90,00:50:58.24
Medals are no defense.

00:51:00.61,00:51:03.07
May I call witnesses to his character?

00:51:03.11,00:51:04.91
You may not.

00:51:04.99,00:51:08.66
But you may call witnesses to the effect[br]that he reached the German wire.

00:51:10.41,00:51:13.33
Mr. President, no one[br]in the entire regiment...

00:51:13.41,00:51:16.58
got anywhere near the German wire,[br]including myself.

00:51:17.38,00:51:19.50
Call the next accused.

00:51:19.59,00:51:21.80
If you're through, Colonel.

00:51:21.84,00:51:24.38
Thank you.

00:51:24.47,00:51:27.68
The prisoner[br]may return to his seat.

00:51:34.97,00:51:39.73
- So you never even left the trenches?[br]- No, sir.

00:51:41.19,00:51:42.11
That's all.

00:51:43.06,00:51:47.32
Corporal Paris,[br]why didn't you leave the trenches?

00:51:48.74,00:51:52.70
Major Vignon was shot, and he fell back[br]on top of me, sir, and knocked me cold.

00:51:52.78,00:51:56.53
And were you lying unconscious in[br]the trenches during the entire attack?

00:51:57.41,00:51:58.41
Yes, sir.

00:52:00.04,00:52:03.00
- That's all.[br]- Have you any witnesses?

00:52:03.96,00:52:09.05
No. Everybody was too busy to notice me,[br]and there were many others lying dead.

00:52:09.13,00:52:13.13
- But you have no witnesses?[br]- No, sir.

00:52:13.22,00:52:16.05
I only have a rather large cut[br]on my head, sir.

00:52:16.13,00:52:18.34
That could've been[br]self-inflicted later.

00:52:20.14,00:52:22.89
Thank you.[br]You may stand down.

00:52:28.48,00:52:30.94
Mr. Prosecutor,[br]you can make your plea.

00:52:36.11,00:52:39.36
Gentlemen of the court...

00:52:39.45,00:52:42.37
this case speaks[br]for itself.

00:52:42.45,00:52:46.37
All of us witnessed the[br]regrettable attack yesterday morning.

00:52:48.95,00:52:53.33
And I submit[br]that that attack...

00:52:53.42,00:52:56.84
was a stain[br]on the flag of France...

00:52:56.92,00:52:59.21
a blot on the honor...

00:52:59.30,00:53:02.63
of every man, woman and child[br]in the French nation.

00:53:05.13,00:53:08.35
It is to us that the sad...

00:53:08.43,00:53:14.14
distressing,[br]repellent duty falls, gentlemen.

00:53:15.31,00:53:17.44
I ask this court...

00:53:17.52,00:53:20.52
to find the accused guilty...

00:53:24.15,00:53:28.20
and impose the penalties prescribed[br]by the code of military justice.

00:53:32.49,00:53:33.99
Thank you.

00:53:35.12,00:53:37.58
Colonel, would you like[br]to make your plea?

00:53:47.71,00:53:50.13
Gentlemen of the court,[br]there are times when I'm ashamed...

00:53:50.21,00:53:54.43
to be a member of the human race,[br]and this is one such occasion.

00:53:56.68,00:54:00.31
It's impossible for me to summarize[br]the case for the defense since...

00:54:00.35,00:54:03.98
the court never allowed me a reasonable[br]opportunity to present my case.

00:54:04.06,00:54:06.98
Are you protesting[br]the authenticity of this court?

00:54:09.81,00:54:11.65
Yes, sir.

00:54:11.73,00:54:14.69
I protest against being prevented[br]from introducing evidence...

00:54:14.78,00:54:18.28
that I consider[br]vital to the defense.

00:54:18.36,00:54:20.16
The prosecution[br]presented no witnesses.

00:54:20.99,00:54:23.16
There has never been a written[br]indictment of charges...

00:54:23.20,00:54:25.58
made against the defendants.

00:54:25.66,00:54:29.33
And lastly I protest[br]against the fact that...

00:54:29.41,00:54:32.42
no stenographic records[br]of this trial have been kept.

00:54:40.92,00:54:46.05
The attack yesterday morning[br]was no stain on the honor of France...

00:54:47.56,00:54:50.93
and certainly no disgrace[br]to the fighting men of this nation.

00:54:51.02,00:54:54.35
But this court martial[br]is such a stain...

00:54:54.44,00:54:56.19
and such a disgrace.

00:54:56.27,00:55:00.27
The case made against these men[br]is a mockery of all human justice.

00:55:00.98,00:55:02.86
Gentlemen of the court...

00:55:02.90,00:55:06.78
to find these men guilty[br]would be a crime...

00:55:07.57,00:55:12.12
to haunt each of you[br]till the day you die.

00:55:15.37,00:55:20.54
I can't believe[br]that the noblest impulse of man--

00:55:20.58,00:55:24.67
his compassion for another--[br]can be completely dead here.

00:55:26.00,00:55:28.92
Therefore I humbly beg you...

00:55:30.42,00:55:33.59
show mercy to these men.

00:55:39.60,00:55:41.89
The accused[br]will be escorted back to the guard room.

00:55:41.98,00:55:45.98
The hearing is closed.[br]The court will now retire to deliberate.

00:55:46.61,00:55:48.61
There will be a guard[br]of six men under arms.

00:55:48.65,00:55:52.11
Rifles loaded, bayonets fixed,[br]two men to each prisoner.

00:55:52.15,00:55:54.49
Any sign of trouble, the prisoners[br]will be instantly covered...

00:55:54.57,00:55:58.53
and if the trouble doesn't subside[br]at once, the prisoner will be shot.

00:55:58.62,00:56:02.04
Everything must go off without a hitch[br]with the least possible delay.

00:56:02.12,00:56:05.91
It shouldn't be hurried.[br]There must be no fumbling around.

00:56:06.00,00:56:09.21
I've been put in charge[br]and made personally responsible...

00:56:09.29,00:56:12.29
for any lack of order[br]or any mistakes.

00:56:12.38,00:56:17.46
But you can take it from me that I shall[br]pass on any blame and with interest...

00:56:17.55,00:56:21.26
to any one of you[br]who fails in his duties.

00:56:21.30,00:56:24.14
The execution[br]will take place at 7:00...

00:56:24.22,00:56:27.14
according to the verdict[br]of the court martial.

00:56:28.81,00:56:31.64
Detail, attention![br]Dismissed!

00:56:45.49,00:56:48.49
- This is compliments of General Mireau.[br]- Duck!

00:56:48.57,00:56:51.79
- Well, tell him thanks.[br]- Don't blame me, soldier.

00:56:52.83,00:56:55.08
Hey, ugly, what are we supposed[br]to eat this with, our fingers?

00:56:55.16,00:56:58.92
The guard says[br]you can't have any knives or forks.

00:56:59.00,00:57:01.13
Is this supposed to be[br]our last meal or something?

00:57:01.21,00:57:05.21
It isn't supposed to be our last meal.[br]It is our last meal.

00:57:05.30,00:57:07.51
This duck is terrific.

00:57:07.59,00:57:09.97
You suppose[br]they'd put anything in the food?

00:57:10.05,00:57:12.55
First they poison us,[br]then they shoot us?

00:57:15.60,00:57:19.31
- I think they put something in it.[br]- Like what?

00:57:19.35,00:57:23.52
Like, uh-- like something[br]to make us groggy or something.

00:57:23.60,00:57:25.77
What would be wrong with that[br]if they did?

00:57:25.86,00:57:29.40
Maybe nothing for you, but I'm[br]going to get out of this somehow.

00:57:29.48,00:57:32.15
- And I don't want to be drugged.[br]- How are you going to get out?

00:57:32.24,00:57:35.53
Chew your way[br]through that stone wall?

00:57:35.61,00:57:38.62
Colonel Dax,[br]he'll see us through.

00:57:40.33,00:57:43.58
Listen, we got to get out of here.[br]They're going to kill us if we don't.

00:57:43.66,00:57:47.25
- Have you got an idea?[br]- No, but there's got to be a way.

00:57:48.54,00:57:51.17
How many guys you think[br]they've got out there?

00:57:51.25,00:57:54.01
They may have a couple of squads. That's[br]what it sounded like this morning.

00:57:54.09,00:57:57.38
- Maybe they're some of our friends.[br]- That's the Third Battalion.

00:57:57.47,00:58:00.80
Anyway, right now[br]we have no friends.

00:58:00.89,00:58:03.85
Why kid yourself?[br]We're not going to get out of this.

00:58:03.93,00:58:07.93
Maybe you're not, but I am.[br]I'll guarantee you of that.

00:58:08.73,00:58:11.19
You see that cockroach?

00:58:11.27,00:58:14.48
Tomorrow morning,[br]we'll be dead and it'll be alive.

00:58:14.56,00:58:17.65
It'll have more contact[br]with my wife and child than I will.

00:58:18.73,00:58:21.65
I'll be nothing,[br]and it'll be alive.

00:58:21.74,00:58:24.70
Now you got the edge on him.

00:58:29.12,00:58:31.95
Good evening, my sons.[br]I'm Father Du Pres.

00:58:35.12,00:58:39.88
- Is there any news?[br]- Yes, I'm afraid I bring you bad news.

00:58:39.96,00:58:42.80
You must prepare for the worst.[br]Colonel Dax asked me to tell you.

00:58:42.88,00:58:45.51
- Oh, mercy, no![br]- He's been in telephone contact...

00:58:45.59,00:58:48.97
with army headquarters but unable[br]to speak to General Broulard...

00:58:49.05,00:58:50.97
or to anyone in authority.

00:58:51.05,00:58:54.39
The same way at Division.[br]No one wants to be found.

00:58:54.47,00:58:57.23
- How much time do we have?[br]- You have plenty of time yet.

00:58:57.31,00:58:59.60
Certainly more than enough[br]to prepare yourselves.

00:59:16.74,00:59:18.74
Father, will you[br]take this letter, please?

00:59:18.83,00:59:20.79
- Of course, my son.[br]- It's to my wife.

00:59:20.87,00:59:23.96
She won't understand this,[br]and I tried to explain it to her.

00:59:24.04,00:59:25.96
I'll see that she gets it.

00:59:26.04,00:59:28.92
Do you want me[br]to hear your confession?

00:59:29.00,00:59:33.46
Well, Father, to tell you the truth,[br]I'm not very religious.

00:59:33.55,00:59:36.01
I know you're trying to help,[br]and I appreciate it...

00:59:36.09,00:59:39.09
but if I started praying now[br]I'd feel like a hypocrite.

00:59:39.18,00:59:41.10
Oh, that's an error, my son.

00:59:41.18,00:59:44.31
God is always ready[br]to listen to your prayers.

00:59:46.81,00:59:50.48
All right, Father.[br]Will you please hear my confession?

00:59:50.56,00:59:52.77
Yes.

00:59:52.81,00:59:57.86
Have faith in your creator, my son.[br]Death comes to us all.

00:59:57.94,00:59:59.74
In the Father, the Son[br]and the Holy Ghost.

00:59:59.82,01:00:03.20
That's really deep:[br]"Death comes to us all."

01:00:03.28,01:00:05.58
That really is deep.

01:00:05.66,01:00:08.29
Ferol, afraid your luck[br]isn't going to hold up?

01:00:08.33,01:00:11.46
Look! This is my religion.

01:00:11.54,01:00:13.83
Oh, great bottle, forgive me my sins,[br]for now I lay me down to sleep.

01:00:13.92,01:00:16.42
Bo-peep. May I drink of you first?[br]Thank you. Amen.

01:00:16.50,01:00:20.84
I understand your anguish, my son, but[br]you must not let it harden your heart.

01:00:20.92,01:00:23.13
May I tell you something, Father?

01:00:23.17,01:00:25.26
Back in my hometown,[br]there was a certain little cafe...

01:00:25.34,01:00:27.72
with an amusing sign[br]over the bar.

01:00:27.80,01:00:28.85
It read,

01:00:28.93,01:00:33.31
"Do not be afraid to ask for credit,[br]for our way of refusing is very polite."

01:00:33.39,01:00:37.23
- Come on. Sit down. You're drunk.[br]- Oh, Paris, leave me alone.

01:00:37.31,01:00:40.36
Can you get out of here[br]with your sanctimonious, pat answers?

01:00:40.44,01:00:43.77
- Are you hanging around to torture us?[br]- No, to help you with all my power.

01:00:43.86,01:00:46.99
- Your power? You have no power![br]- No, but God has power.

01:00:47.07,01:00:49.74
- Does he? What a laugh![br]- You can be saved.

01:00:49.82,01:00:52.53
Saved? I'll be saved?

01:00:54.20,01:00:56.74
Cut it out, Arnaud!

01:01:07.21,01:01:10.71
Father, get a doctor.[br]Quick.

01:01:19.30,01:01:22.64
That should keep him quiet long enough.[br]That's a nasty skull fracture, though.

01:01:22.72,01:01:26.10
- He may not live out the night.[br]- What are we supposed to do with him?

01:01:26.19,01:01:29.94
My advice is to tie him to a stretcher[br]so he won't slip when you tilt it.

01:01:30.02,01:01:33.07
Surely they won't execute[br]a man in that condition.

01:01:33.15,01:01:37.65
The sentence will be carried out.[br]I've already checked with the general.

01:01:37.74,01:01:41.70
If he's still alive in the morning,[br]pinch his cheeks a couple of times.

01:01:41.78,01:01:44.66
It may make him open his eyes.[br]The general wants him to be conscious.

01:01:46.62,01:01:48.16
Yes?

01:01:50.75,01:01:53.71
- Lieutenant Roget reporting, sir.[br]- Come in.

01:01:54.79,01:01:57.34
Sergeant Boulanger[br]said you wanted to see me, sir.

01:01:57.42,01:02:01.76
Yes. We have a pretty unpleasant thing[br]on our hands in a few hours.

01:02:02.59,01:02:05.59
- You mean the execution?[br]- Yes.

01:02:05.68,01:02:07.72
Yes, sir.[br]It's very unfortunate.

01:02:07.80,01:02:11.22
Very unfortunate.[br]That's just how I feel about it.

01:02:11.31,01:02:14.02
- None of us are happy about it, sir.[br]- How'd you happen...

01:02:14.10,01:02:15.89
to pick Corporal Paris?

01:02:16.98,01:02:18.90
I-- I had to pick somebody, sir.

01:02:18.98,01:02:21.69
That's right. Of course,[br]you had no personal motive...

01:02:21.73,01:02:23.94
in picking Paris,[br]did you?

01:02:24.99,01:02:27.90
You picked him[br]because he was a coward, didn't you?

01:02:29.32,01:02:31.91
Did you or didn't you?

01:02:31.99,01:02:34.04
Yes, sir. I did.

01:02:34.12,01:02:38.54
Well, like you say,[br]somebody had to be picked.

01:02:38.62,01:02:42.25
- It was quite a problem, sir.[br]- Yes, I have the same kind of problem.

01:02:42.33,01:02:45.17
I have to pick someone to be in charge[br]of the firing squad tomorrow.

01:02:45.25,01:02:47.46
Do you have any objections[br]to taking the job?

01:02:48.63,01:02:51.22
- Me, sir?[br]- Yes, you.

01:02:53.55,01:02:55.30
Don't you feel well?

01:02:55.39,01:02:58.85
We-- No-- Yeah, I feel all right, sir.[br]It's just that l--

01:02:58.93,01:03:01.68
I-Is it too hot in here?[br]Would you like me to open a window?

01:03:03.39,01:03:08.02
Well, it's just that I've never been[br]in charge of a firing squad before, sir.

01:03:09.19,01:03:13.61
There's nothing to it. First you help[br]the sergeant tie the men to the post...

01:03:13.69,01:03:18.74
and offer the men blindfolds--[br]if they want them, you tie them on.

01:03:18.78,01:03:21.99
Now, you take your position with[br]the firing squad, you raise your sword:

01:03:22.08,01:03:25.16
Ready, aim, fire.

01:03:25.25,01:03:28.41
Then you draw your revolver out,[br]walk forward...

01:03:28.50,01:03:30.79
and put a bullet[br]through each man's head.

01:03:32.08,01:03:35.46
Sir, I request that I be excused[br]from this duty.

01:03:35.55,01:03:37.63
Request denied.

01:03:37.71,01:03:40.63
- Colonel, l--[br]- You've got the job. It's all yours.

01:03:40.68,01:03:42.64
- That's all.[br]- Colonel, if you could just--

01:03:42.68,01:03:43.97
That's all!

01:03:44.80,01:03:46.64
Yes?

01:03:46.72,01:03:48.72
Excuse me, sir.[br]Colonel Dax?

01:03:48.81,01:03:51.35
- Yes?[br]- My name is Rousseau, sir.

01:03:51.43,01:03:54.90
- Captain of Artillery.[br]- What is it, Captain?

01:04:00.19,01:04:03.99
I have something to tell you that may[br]have a bearing on the court martial.

01:04:05.15,01:04:06.74
Come in.

01:05:01.41,01:05:03.29
Colonel. Good evening.

01:05:03.37,01:05:05.66
- Good evening.[br]- Come and sit down.

01:05:05.75,01:05:08.96
Thank you, sir. I-- I'm really sorry[br]to intrude on you in this way.

01:05:09.04,01:05:12.21
Not at all. Always delighted to see you,[br]Colonel Dax. Will you have a cigar?

01:05:12.25,01:05:14.46
No, thank you, sir.

01:05:14.55,01:05:17.76
- Well, l--[br]- Think you'll find it delicious.

01:05:17.84,01:05:20.30
I must apologize for not inviting you[br]to the party tonight...

01:05:20.38,01:05:23.72
but I'm afraid that it's[br]a dress affair.

01:05:23.76,01:05:25.56
Thank you, sir,[br]but I must confess...

01:05:25.64,01:05:29.10
that this is not entirely[br]a social visit.

01:05:29.18,01:05:33.73
Come, Dax.[br]Let's not go over all that ground again.

01:05:34.73,01:05:37.32
Though, I must admit[br]that judging....

01:05:37.40,01:05:40.40
from the casualties, the efforts of your[br]regiment must have been considerable.

01:05:40.49,01:05:43.86
How can you understand that[br]and allow these men to be shot tomorrow?

01:05:43.90,01:05:46.78
Come, Colonel, you're choosing[br]to take a rather simple view of this.

01:05:46.87,01:05:51.20
The attack was impossible.[br]The general staff must have known that.

01:05:52.41,01:05:56.79
Colonel Dax, we think[br]we're doing a good job running the war.

01:05:56.87,01:06:00.88
You must be aware the general staff[br]is subject to unfair pressures...

01:06:00.92,01:06:02.96
from newspapers and politicians.

01:06:03.05,01:06:05.92
Maybe the attack against the Ant Hill[br]was impossible.

01:06:06.01,01:06:08.18
Perhaps it was an error of judgment[br]on our part.

01:06:08.26,01:06:12.35
On the other hand, if your men had been[br]more daring, they might have taken it.

01:06:12.43,01:06:14.93
Who knows? In any case...

01:06:15.01,01:06:18.77
why should we have to bear any more[br]criticism than we have to?

01:06:18.85,01:06:22.40
Aside from the fact that many of[br]your men never left the trenches...

01:06:22.48,01:06:24.94
there's the troops' morale,[br]don't forget.

01:06:24.98,01:06:26.94
- The troops' morale?[br]- Certainly.

01:06:27.02,01:06:29.99
These executions will be a perfect tonic[br]for the entire division.

01:06:30.07,01:06:32.65
There are few things more fundamentally[br]encouraging and stimulating...

01:06:32.74,01:06:34.57
than seeing someone else die.

01:06:34.66,01:06:37.66
- I never thought of that, sir.[br]- Colonel, troops are like children.

01:06:37.74,01:06:42.33
Just as a child wants his father[br]to be firm, troops crave discipline.

01:06:42.41,01:06:45.29
One way to maintain discipline[br]is to shoot a man now and then.

01:06:46.17,01:06:48.84
May I ask...

01:06:48.92,01:06:51.88
do you sincerely believe[br]the things you've said?

01:06:56.84,01:06:58.76
It's been a pleasure[br]discussing this with you, Colonel...

01:06:58.84,01:07:02.22
but I'm afraid that I'd better[br]be getting back to my guests.

01:07:02.30,01:07:05.22
Forgive me for having kept you[br]from your party.

01:07:07.27,01:07:10.98
Oh, by the way, sir,[br]have you heard that General Mireau...

01:07:11.02,01:07:14.40
ordered his own battery commander,[br]Captain Rousseau...

01:07:14.48,01:07:17.65
to open fire on his own positions[br]during the attack?

01:07:21.24,01:07:24.49
Of course, the captain refused[br]without a written order.

01:07:24.53,01:07:27.95
But General Mireau demanded that[br]he commence firing on our own trenches.

01:07:27.99,01:07:31.37
Well, again, Rousseau refused[br]without an order in writing...

01:07:31.45,01:07:35.71
but again he was ordered[br]and again he refused...

01:07:35.79,01:07:37.50
all in front of witnesses.

01:07:37.58,01:07:40.34
Do you actually[br]believe this fantastic story?

01:07:40.38,01:07:44.51
Here are copies of the sworn statements[br]from all the principals involved.

01:07:44.59,01:07:48.30
Battery Commander Rousseau, Captain[br]Nichols, the artillery spotter...

01:07:48.34,01:07:52.18
the telephone clerk[br]and my own deposition.

01:07:52.26,01:07:56.39
What has this got to do with the charge[br]against the condemned prisoners?

01:07:56.48,01:08:00.15
A general in a tantrum over the failure[br]of an impossible attack...

01:08:00.19,01:08:03.98
orders his artillery[br]to fire on his own men.

01:08:04.02,01:08:07.86
The same officer on the same day[br]orders a court martial...

01:08:07.94,01:08:11.95
in which three of his men[br]are sentenced to be shot.

01:08:12.03,01:08:17.12
General, what would your newspapers[br]and your politicians do with that?

01:08:18.20,01:08:21.91
- Are you trying to blackmail me?[br]- Sir, that's an ugly word...

01:08:22.00,01:08:24.75
but you are in a difficult position.

01:08:24.83,01:08:28.92
Too much has happened. Someone's[br]got to be hurt. The question is whom.

01:08:31.05,01:08:34.05
General Mireau's[br]assault on the Ant Hill failed.

01:08:34.13,01:08:37.89
His order to fire on his own troops[br]was refused.

01:08:37.97,01:08:40.39
But his attempt[br]to murder three innocent men...

01:08:40.43,01:08:44.89
to protect his own reputation will be[br]prevented by the general staff.

01:08:52.06,01:08:56.40
Will you pardon me, Colonel Dax?[br]I've been rude to my guests too long.

01:09:23.63,01:09:25.55
Detail, halt!

01:09:26.89,01:09:29.51
Order, arms!

01:09:29.60,01:09:31.52
Fall out.

01:09:57.04,01:10:00.08
Courage, my sons.[br]The worst is over.

01:10:11.42,01:10:14.09
Good morning, Paris.

01:10:14.13,01:10:17.93
Good morning, Sergeant.[br]How are you today?

01:10:18.01,01:10:20.72
Not too bad. How are you?

01:10:23.85,01:10:26.19
You missed some good chow[br]in here last night.

01:10:26.27,01:10:28.61
What did you have?

01:10:30.98,01:10:33.82
Have you got a drink for us?

01:10:33.86,01:10:36.32
Take a swig of this.

01:10:39.66,01:10:43.16
It just occurred to me.[br]Funny thing. I--

01:10:43.24,01:10:46.12
I haven't had one sexual thought[br]since the court martial.

01:10:46.16,01:10:49.33
It's pretty extraordinary,[br]isn't it?

01:10:49.41,01:10:51.25
Act like a man.

01:10:53.08,01:10:56.17
- Listen, Paris. Are you listening?[br]- Yes.

01:10:56.25,01:10:58.34
There will be a lot of dignitaries,[br]newspapermen out there.

01:10:58.42,01:11:00.51
How do you want to be remembered?

01:11:01.34,01:11:03.89
- I don't want to die.[br]- Many of us will be joining you...

01:11:03.97,01:11:05.47
before this war's over.

01:11:05.55,01:11:08.01
I don't care.[br]I don't want to die.

01:11:09.10,01:11:13.60
- Please save me, Sergeant.[br]- I can't save you. No one can now.

01:11:15.10,01:11:17.90
This is the last decision[br]you'll have a chance to make on earth.

01:11:17.98,01:11:21.57
You can act like a man,[br]or we'll have to drag you out of here.

01:11:21.65,01:11:24.57
In the end, it will all be the same.[br]It's up to you.

01:11:41.08,01:11:45.80
Let's get busy. You and Ferol take your[br]coats off. No use hanging around here.

01:12:03.85,01:12:06.56
...with the help of Thy grace[br]to do penance...

01:12:06.65,01:12:09.19
to amend my life.

01:12:16.49,01:12:18.91
What do I have to die for, Father?

01:12:21.99,01:12:25.20
What do I have to die for?[br]I didn't do anything wr--

01:12:25.25,01:12:28.33
We do not question[br]the will of God, my son.

01:12:28.42,01:12:32.59
But I fought. I fought.[br]I fought on the battlefield.

01:12:32.67,01:12:36.17
Why don't they die?[br]Why don't they put them to death?

01:12:36.26,01:12:38.72
You showed courage in the face[br]of the enemy, my son.

01:12:38.80,01:12:40.68
Show it now before your own troops.

01:12:40.76,01:12:43.18
But I'm scared.[br]I'm scared.

01:12:44.51,01:12:47.56
Oh, Father, I'm scared.

01:12:47.64,01:12:51.02
Courage. Brace yourself.[br]Man, brace yourself.

01:12:58.77,01:13:02.61
He said, "This day,[br]thou shalt be with me in paradise."

01:13:02.65,01:13:07.57
- Really, Father?[br]- Yes, my son.

01:13:08.87,01:13:12.08
I'll never see my wife again,[br]Father.

01:13:13.66,01:13:16.83
I'll never see nobody again,[br]Father.

01:13:16.92,01:13:19.33
Courage, man.[br]Brace yourself.

01:13:19.42,01:13:22.00
- I can't help it.[br]- Brace yourself, man.

01:13:22.09,01:13:27.09
- I can't help it, Father.[br]- Oh, God, Almighty God.

01:13:27.17,01:13:31.01
- Oh, Christ. Strengthen me, God![br]- Grant courage to this man...

01:13:31.09,01:13:32.80
who is about to die.

01:13:39.48,01:13:42.40
What do I have to die for,[br]Father?

01:13:44.94,01:13:46.98
What do I have to die for?

01:13:47.07,01:13:49.86
Forward, face!

01:13:59.78,01:14:01.95
Secure the men!

01:14:04.83,01:14:06.71
Detail, attention!

01:14:06.79,01:14:09.33
Forward, march!

01:14:17.84,01:14:19.43
Detail...

01:14:21.89,01:14:22.97
halt!

01:14:23.05,01:14:25.14
Left, face!

01:14:27.64,01:14:29.23
Repent.

01:14:59.54,01:15:02.42
In the name of the French people...

01:15:02.50,01:15:06.59
Corporal Phillip Paris,[br]Private Maurice Ferol...

01:15:06.68,01:15:10.97
and Private Pierre Arnaud[br]of the 701st Regiment...

01:15:11.05,01:15:16.14
having been found guilty of cowardice[br]in the face of the enemy...

01:15:16.22,01:15:19.44
are to be executed[br]by rifle fire immediately...

01:15:19.52,01:15:23.36
in accordance with the judgment[br]of the military court martial.

01:15:53.46,01:15:55.93
You want a blindfold?

01:15:56.01,01:15:59.43
Yes, Lieutenant. Please.

01:16:04.22,01:16:06.60
I don't want to die.

01:16:19.57,01:16:22.57
Did-- Did you want a blindfold?

01:16:25.45,01:16:27.41
I'm sorry.

01:16:50.64,01:16:52.56
Oh, Father.

01:17:05.40,01:17:06.99
Ready!

01:17:09.86,01:17:11.16
Aim!

01:17:13.32,01:17:14.95
Fire!

01:17:18.66,01:17:20.91
I'm awfully glad[br]you could be there, George.

01:17:21.00,01:17:23.79
This sort of thing[br]is always rather grim.

01:17:23.83,01:17:26.00
But this had splendor,[br]don't you think?

01:17:26.09,01:17:28.50
I have never seen an affair[br]of this sort handled any better.

01:17:29.46,01:17:32.63
The men died wonderfully.[br]There's always that chance...

